I learned about constructors, instance variables, instance methods, and the self keyword in Python.
A constructor is a special method in a class called __init__. 
It is automatically executed when an object of the class is created. 
The main purpose of a constructor is to initialize the attributes of an object.
Instance variables are variables that belong to each object of a class. 
They store the data specific to that object.
In the example of the SmartLight system, attributes like room name, brightness, and status are stored as instance variables.
Instance methods are functions defined inside a class that operate on object data.
These methods allow objects to perform actions, such as turning the light on or off and displaying the light details.
The self keyword represents the current object of the class.
It is used to access instance variables and methods inside the class. Using self ensures that each object maintains its own data and behavior.
